===Narrations===
McCullough has narrated many television shows and documentaries throughout his career. In addition to narrating the 2003 film ''[[Seabiscuit (film)|Seabiscuit]]'', McCullough hosted [[PBS]]<nowiki>'</nowiki>s ''[[American Experience]]'' from 1988<U+2013>1999.<ref name="CNNja"/> McCullough has also narrated numerous documentaries directed by [[Ken Burns]], including [[Emmy Award]] winning ''[[The Civil War (TV series)|The Civil War]]'',<ref name="CNNja"/> [[Academy Award]] nominated ''[[Brooklyn Bridge (film)|Brooklyn Bridge]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.pbs.org/kenburns/brooklynbridge/about/|title= Brooklyn Bridge: About the Film|accessdate=2008-06-19 |author= |date= |work= |publisher=[[PBS]]}}</ref> ''[[The Statue of Liberty (documentary)|The Statue of Liberty]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.pbs.org/kenburns/statueofliberty/about/|title= The Statue of Liberty: About the Film|accessdate=2008-06-19 |author= |date= |work= |publisher=[[PBS]]}}</ref> and ''[[The Congress (film)|The Congress]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.pbs.org/kenburns/congress/about/|title= The Congress: About the Film|accessdate=2008-06-19 |author= |date= |work= |publisher=[[PBS]]}}</ref>

====List of films presented or narrated====
* ''[[Brooklyn Bridge (film)|Brooklyn Bridge]]'' (1981)
* ''[[Smithsonian World]]'' (5 episodes, 1984<U+2013>1988)
* ''[[The Shakers: Hands to Work, Hearts to God]]'' (1984)
* ''[[The Statue of Liberty (documentary)|The Statue of Liberty]]'' (1985)
* ''[[Huey Long (documentary)|Huey Long]]'' (1985)
* ''[[The Congress (film)|The Congress]]'' (1988)
